name: Instant Pot® Brunswick Stew
author: Ross Iversen McLeod
summary: Brunswick stew is an Eastern NC favorite, made simple in the Instant Pot®!
ingredients: 2  russet potatoes, peeled and diced, or more to taste
½ teaspoon red pepper flakes, or to taste
¼ teaspoon seasoned salt, or to taste
1 (10 ounce) package frozen baby lima beans
¾ cup shredded cooked pork, or to taste
directions: Combine tomatoes, potatoes, chicken broth, onion, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, ketchup, and red pepper flakes in the pot of a multi-functional pressure cooker (such as Instant Pot®)
Lay chicken breasts on top; add seasoned salt, thyme, and black pepper
Select high pressure according to manufacturer's instructions; set timer for 20 minutes
Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build
Release pressure carefully using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, about 5 minutes
Remove chicken from pot and set on a plate to cool
Place corn, lima beans, and okra into the pot and stir to combine
Remove skin from chicken, shred the meat off the bones, and return to the pot
Seal cooker; select low pressure and cook until vegetables are heated through, about 15 minutes
Release pressure carefully using the quick-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, about 5 minutes
